Why do we have to use the ```/``` operator at all?  The change in sign for the exponent is already sufficient.  Looking at the ```ScaleConverter``` class (https://github.com/hgrecco/pint/blob/master/pint/converters.py#28), why not store the exponent instead of the scalar integer like so:
```python
class ScaleBase10Converter(ScaleConverter):
    """A linear transformation for base 10 conversion
    """

    is_multiplicative = True

    def __init__(self, exponent):
        self.exponent = exponent
        self.scale = 10 ** self.exponent

    def from_reference(self, value, inplace=False):
        if inplace:
            value *= 10 ** (-1 * self.exponent)
        else:
            value = value * 10 ** (-1 * self.exponent)

        return value
```

