@alexmojaki I don't see your issue as being similar. You should be able to do what you want by using something like:

```
@wrapt.decorator
def _real_decorator(wrapped, instance, args, kwargs):
    # can access wrapped.attribute here
    return wrapped(*args, **kwargs)

def attach(value):
    def real_decorator(wrapped):
        wrapped.attribute = value
        return _real_decorator(wrapped)
    return real_decorator
```

Do be mindful of multithreading issues if the attribute is not read only.

Also look at other ways of dealing with decorator arguments in:

* http://wrapt.readthedocs.org/en/latest/decorators.html#decorators-with-arguments
* http://wrapt.readthedocs.org/en/latest/decorators.html#decorators-with-optional-arguments

