I am slightly unsure of your question. If you are looking to use the same embedding (i.e the same model parameters), you can just use the same text field embedder for both `TextFields` and use the same namespace for both `TextFields`. 

If you want to have two separate sets of parameters which are initialized using the same pre-trained vectors, you can just have two separate `TokenEmbedders`, both of which are embeddings.

Example:
```
   // These have different parameters, but are initialised using the same pre-trained vectors.
    "text_field_embedder1": {
      "key_of_the_token_indexer_for_text_field_1": {
        "type": "embedding",
        "pretrained_file": "/glove/glove.6B.100d.txt.gz",
        "embedding_dim": 100,
        "trainable": false
      }
},
   "text_field_embedder2": {
      "key_of_the_token_indexer_for_text_field_2": {
        "type": "embedding",
        "pretrained_file": "same/path/to/glove/vectors",
        "embedding_dim": 100
        }
}
```
If you want to share the embedding, just use the same namespace for both text fields and have a single `TextFieldEmbedder` which you apply twice in your model (and therefore only have one of these text_field_embedders in the JSON config above). Hopefully one of these is your use case!

You are however correct that this results in reading the glove vectors in twice, which is unfortunate - we hadn't run in to this issue. Let us know if it really slows you down, e.g you want to have many namespaces which differ but share glove vectors. Hopefully this solves your problem in the short term.

@bacongobbler we didn't hit any use case with Fleet node failover  that has registry, as the systemD unit file dynamically  gets the registry Ip and Port and appends image to it. This is not the case with other schedulers like swarm, kubernetes or Marathon. We have to specify image at the time of creation and its static.
 For Example, registry IP and port are (172.17.8.100:5000) app image X at the time of creation will be 172.17.8.100:5000/X and node that has registry failed and scheduler started registry on different node and Ip changed to 172.17.8.101. Now the schedulers will try to reschedule the apps on the failed node by pulling image from 172.17.8.100:5000 but not 172.17.8.101:5000.

This is something we need to address in the future and movign to URL based Registry is one of the solutions

