Hi @mnips thanks for the suggestion! I think this can be done with a `TimeDependent` arrival distribution:

```
def arrival_schedules(t):
    if t <= 10:
        return random.expovariate(0.4)
    if t < 40:
        return random.expovariate(0.2)
    if t < 100:
        return random.expovariate(0.3)
```

And then include this in the `Arrival_distributions`:

```
Arrival_distributions=[['TimeDependent`, arrival_schedules]]
```

More info on time dependent distributions here: http://ciw.readthedocs.io/en/latest/Guides/time_dependent.html

